# S11c-prereq (2026-05-13) → v5: categoria `uncensored` (blueprint sez 15.11 heretic-handler).
# S170 (2026-05-14) → v5.1: 3 field_change applied from routing-drift run 20260514T055152Z.
#   1. gemini-2.5-flash context_window 1000000 → 1048576 (upstream accuracy)
#   2. gemini-2.5-pro context_window 1000000 → 1048576 (upstream accuracy)
#   3. meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free context_window 131072 → 65536 (REGRESSION -50%, see notes)
# Aggiornamento runtime: routing-refresh notturno (CLAUDE.md "vincoli invarianti").
# Vincolo #1: ogni entry ha last_verified + sources upstream verificati.
# Vincolo #5: free-tier first, soglia hard €30/mese tracciata in state/costs.jsonl.
# S175 (2026-05-15) POLICY demand-driven role addition:
#   Nuovo `role:` aggiunto SOLO quando ≥1 componente VOS attivo dichiara dependency
#   nel proprio source. NO ruoli speculativi (reasoning/coding/vision/cheap) senza
#   consumer reale. Verifica consumer prima di aggiungere:
#     grep -r "_resolve_chain(role='<NAME>')" components/
#   Motivazione: audit S172 Gap #4 deload S175 dopo verifica 0/13 consumer per
#   ruoli generic listati. Vedi wiki/notes/S175-gaps-3-4-deload.md.

version: 5.1
last_verified: 2026-05-14
last_verified_method: real_http_call  # vincolo #11, no doc-only
# S8 FASE 2.1 (2026-05-12) routing-http-verify.py: 5/5 verified post key setup
#   google  gemini-2.5-flash               → verified (present in /v1beta/models)
#   google  gemini-2.5-pro                 → verified catalog, paid quota Luke
#   cerebras llama3.1-8b                   → verified (present in /v1/models)
#   cerebras qwen-3-235b-a22b-instruct-2507 → verified catalog, quota too low free
#   openrouter llama-3.3-70b:free          → verified post key setup S8 (scope: VOS only)
# Drift count: 0 — nessuna deviation upstream-vs-locale. Log: state/routing-drift.jsonl
# Fallback chain long_context aggiornata: gemini-flash → openrouter-70b → gemini-pro.

# S5c reval esito: Gemini 2.5 Flash CONFERMATO long_context primario.
# Alternative valutate (vincolo #2 ricerca attiva max 5min, deviation S5b "vendor-lock-in"):
#  - Llama 3.3 70B self-hosted iMac → ESCLUSO: no AVX2 (machdep.cpu.features=AVX1.0),
#    RAM 16GB < 40GB richiesti per 70B Q4. Capacity reale, non capex.
#  - HF Colab T4 (skill free-gpu-api esistente) → ESCLUSO: 15GB VRAM = max 8B Q4,
#    qualità degradata su 105K context consolidamento.
#  - Cerebras Llama 3.3 70B → CANDIDATO PAID-BACKUP: 128K ctx (sufficiente per
#    Guardian/FLUXION, marginale ARGOS 175K), 1M tok/day free, >2000 tok/s.
#    HTTP test BLOCCATO da assenza CEREBRAS_API_KEY. Setup → S5d.
#  - OpenRouter Llama 3.3 70B free → CANDIDATO PAID-BACKUP: 131K ctx, 20 req/min.
#    HTTP test BLOCCATO da assenza OPENROUTER_API_KEY. Setup → S5d.
# Decisione: Gemini flash resta vincente per 1M ctx unico + free tier 250 RPD vs
# 1.2% quota usata (3 call/giorno). Backup chain configurata sotto, attivabile S5d.

models:
  # Long-context model per pattern compilation Karpathy (handoff debt >2000 righe).
  # Requisito: ≥500K context per leggere ~15K righe ARGOS senza chunking.
  - role: long_context
    model_id: gemini-2.5-flash
    provider: google
    api_endpoint: https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta
    context_window: 1048576  # S170 drift apply: was 1000000, upstream confirms 1048576
    output_tokens_max: 65536
    cost_per_1m_in: 0.0
    cost_per_1m_out: 0.0
    free_tier: true
    rate_limit_rpm: 10
    rate_limit_rpd: 250
    rate_limit_tpm: 250000
    auth_env: GEMINI_API_KEY
    last_verified: 2026-05-14
    last_verified_method: real_http_call  # S8 routing-http-verify: catalog match
    sources:
      - https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/rate-limits
      - https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-2.5-flash
    notes: |
      VERIFICATO 2026-05-09 con HTTP call reale: gemini-2.5-flash → HTTP 200 (key Luke).
      gemini-2.5-pro NON disponibile su free tier del progetto Google di Luke
      (HTTP 429, "limit: 0" sul free_tier_input_token_count). Switch a flash.
      Stesso 1M context window di pro, qualità reasoning marginalmente inferiore
      ma sufficiente per Karpathy compilation (consolidare handoff già scritti,
      non generation creativa). Spot-check manuale del primo COMPILED-STATE.md
      è obbligatorio per validare output.
      Free tier: 10 RPM, 250 RPD, 250K TPM (verified docs ufficiali).
      Karpathy use case: ~3 chiamate/settimana max → 250 RPD copre largamente.

  # Fallback paid se Luke attiva billing futuro
  - role: long_context_paid_fallback
    model_id: gemini-2.5-pro
    provider: google
    api_endpoint: https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta
    context_window: 1048576  # S170 drift apply: was 1000000, upstream confirms 1048576
    output_tokens_max: 65536
    cost_per_1m_in: 1.25  # tier ≤200K input
    cost_per_1m_out: 10.0
    free_tier: false
    auth_env: GEMINI_API_KEY
    last_verified: 2026-05-14
    last_verified_method: real_http_call  # S8: presente in /v1beta/models, paid quota
    sources:
      - https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/pricing
    notes: |
      Solo se Luke attiva billing Google Cloud. NON usare di default.
      Soglia hard €30/mese: ~24 chiamate/mese da 200K input + 50K output.

  # S5e Cerebras setup HTTP-verified (deviation "cerebras-model-names-doc-vs-real"):
  # - Doc S5c citava llama-3.3-70b → /v1/models REALE non lo lista.
  # - Modelli reali tier free Luke: zai-glm-4.7, gpt-oss-120b (404 access),
  #   llama3.1-8b (OK 2401 tok/s), qwen-3-235b-a22b-instruct-2507 (RPM quota troppo bassa).
  # - Llama 3.1 8B inadatto a long_context (consolidamento 100K+ input richiede 70B+).
  # - Conclusione: Cerebras NON sostituisce Gemini flash come long_context primary.
  #   Si riposiziona come fast_short_context per task brevi a bassa latenza.

  - role: fast_short_context
    model_id: llama3.1-8b
    provider: cerebras
    api_endpoint: https://api.cerebras.ai/v1
    context_window: 128000  # context architetturale; use case ≤8K input per latenza
    output_tokens_max: 8192
    cost_per_1m_in: 0.0
    cost_per_1m_out: 0.0
    free_tier: true
    auth_env: CEREBRAS_API_KEY
    required_headers:
      User-Agent: venture-os/1.0  # Cloudflare 1010 senza UA custom
    last_verified: 2026-05-12
    last_verified_method: real_http_call  # S8 routing-http-verify: catalog match
    sources:
      - https://api.cerebras.ai/v1/models  # /v1/models live (vincolo #1)
      - https://inference-docs.cerebras.ai/introduction
    notes: |
      Use case: brief/routing/classification con input ≤8K, latenza <300ms.
      Speed verificato 2401 tok/s su prompt 41 tok / output 3 tok (2026-05-11).
      NON usare per consolidamento handoff: 8B reasoning su 50K+ è inadeguato.
      Cloudflare blocca User-Agent default Python — header UA obbligatorio.

  - role: long_context_backup_unavailable_cerebras
    model_id: qwen-3-235b-a22b-instruct-2507
    provider: cerebras
    api_endpoint: https://api.cerebras.ai/v1
    context_window: 131072
    free_tier: true
    free_tier_quota_too_low: true  # 3 retry consecutivi 429 request_quota_exceeded
    auth_env: CEREBRAS_API_KEY
    last_verified: 2026-05-12
    last_verified_method: real_http_call  # S8: catalog match, quota free insuff.
    notes: |
      Modello esiste in /v1/models ma free-tier RPM quota insufficiente per produzione.
      Auth OK, errore 429 request_quota_exceeded persistente. Non in fallback chain.
      Riconsiderare se Luke passa a paid tier Cerebras.

  - role: long_context_backup_openrouter
    model_id: meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free
    provider: openrouter
    api_endpoint: https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
    context_window: 65536  # S170 drift: REGRESSION upstream da 131072 → 65536 (-50%)
    output_tokens_max: 4096
    cost_per_1m_in: 0.0
    cost_per_1m_out: 0.0
    free_tier: true
    rate_limit_rpm: 20
    auth_env: OPENROUTER_API_KEY
    last_verified: 2026-05-14
    last_verified_method: real_http_call  # S8: catalog match, key setupata
    sources:
      - https://openrouter.ai/models?q=llama-3.3
    notes: |
      VERIFICATO 2026-05-12 S8 routing-http-verify: presente in /v1/models OpenRouter.
      ⚠️ S170 DRIFT REGRESSION 2026-05-14: upstream ha dimezzato context_window
      da 131072 a 65536. Impatto Karpathy compilation: input max ridotto a ~50K righe
      (era ~100K). Per ARGOS handoff >50K righe servono chunking 2-pass o fallback
      a gemini-flash 1M ctx. NON cambia priority chain (gemini-flash primary 1M
      basta solo da solo). Backup secondario ora ancora più marginale.
      Scope chiave: VOS only (preferenza Luke, non enforced server-side).
      Caveat persistente: output_tokens_max=4096 inferiore a Gemini (65536).
      Trigger riconsiderare chain: se OpenRouter introduce variante :free con
      ctx ≥131K e RPM ≥20 (es. qwen3-next-80b candidate S170 model_added).

  # S11c-prereq (2026-05-13) — heretic-handler uncensored chain.
  # Blueprint sez 15.11 + sez 232-235. Use case: brainstorming strategico ARGOS
  # (persona fittizia, content trojan-horse, pricing aggressivo, sales psychology)
  # senza filtri commerciali Anthropic. Gate hardcoded ALLOWED_CATEGORIES nel
  # componente, audit hash-only in state/heretic-log.jsonl (no raw content).
  # _resolve_chain(role='uncensored') ritorna TUTTE le entry con role match,
  # in ordine YAML → dolphin primary, hermes fallback.
  # Pre-flight S11c-prereq 2026-05-13: entrambi /v1/models OpenRouter OK.
  - role: uncensored
    provider: openrouter
    model_id: cognitivecomputations/dolphin-mistral-24b-venice-edition:free
    api_endpoint: https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
    auth_env: OPENROUTER_API_KEY
    context_window: 32768
    input_tokens_max: 32768
    output_tokens_max: 4096
    cost_per_1m_in: 0.0
    cost_per_1m_out: 0.0
    free_tier: true
    last_verified: 2026-05-13
    last_verified_method: real_http_call
    sources:
      - https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models
      - https://openrouter.ai/cognitivecomputations/dolphin-mistral-24b-venice-edition:free
    notes: |
      Venice-edition uncensored fine-tune di Mistral 24B by cognitivecomputations.
      Free tier OpenRouter, 32K context. Primary heretic-handler.
      Scope etico: NON è bypass per content illegale. ALLOWED_CATEGORIES
      hardcoded nel handler limita a brainstorming commerciale borderline
      (persona-fittizia, content-strategy, pricing-aggressivo,
      scope-borderline-legal, sales-psychology, competitor-positioning,
      brainstorm-generale). Audit append-only hash-only.

  - role: uncensored
    provider: openrouter
    model_id: nousresearch/hermes-3-llama-3.1-405b:free
    api_endpoint: https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
    auth_env: OPENROUTER_API_KEY
    context_window: 131072
    input_tokens_max: 131072
    output_tokens_max: 4096
    cost_per_1m_in: 0.0
    cost_per_1m_out: 0.0
    free_tier: true
    last_verified: 2026-05-13
    last_verified_method: real_http_call
    sources:
      - https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/models
      - https://openrouter.ai/nousresearch/hermes-3-llama-3.1-405b:free
    notes: |
      Fallback. Hermes 3 405B by NousResearch — neutrally-aligned, low-refusal,
      131K context (utile per brainstorming con context lungo da wiki ARGOS).
      Scatta su rate_limit/error del dolphin primary via _resolve_chain
      (entrambe entry hanno role='uncensored', ordine YAML = ordine chain).

defaults:
  long_context: gemini-2.5-flash
  long_context_fallback_chain:  # ordine di attivazione su rate limit/errore
    - gemini-2.5-flash                          # primario, free 250 RPD verified
    - meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free    # S8 verified, openrouter 131K ctx, 20 RPM
    - gemini-2.5-pro                            # paid fallback, solo se Luke attiva billing
    # NB S5e: Cerebras rimosso da chain long_context (modelli ≤8B free tier inadeguati).
    # NB S8 2026-05-12: openrouter llama-3.3-70b:free aggiunto come backup #2 free
    # (output max 4096 — adapter VOS deve gestire chunking output se >4K tokens).
  fast_short_context: llama3.1-8b  # cerebras, latenza ottimale per task brevi
